{
  "texts": [
    "For example, DKL performs the best for the ESM2 encoding, but these models have the least calibrated uncertainties and the highest MAEs.",
    "The poor calibration of DKL models may result from some mode collapse where out-of-distribution inputs are mapped close to the training representations by the neural network 55.",
    "Because calibration is measured on the entire combinatorial design space, it may not directly correspond to the ability to find an optimal variant.",
    "Overall, ALDE is an effective method for navigating protein fitness landscapes, and it offers several advantages compared to DE.",
    "First, ALDE can unlock engineering outcomes not possible with simple DE."
  ]
}